experiment 1.1 contain duplicate (leetcode problem 217)
aim:Given an integer array nums, return true if any value appears at least twice in the array, and return false if every element is distinct.
algorithm:
1.Sort the array in ascending order.
2.Traverse the array from index 1 to n-1.
3.For each index i:
4.If nums[i] == nums[i-1], return true (duplicate found).
5.If the loop finishes without finding any duplicate, return false.
code:
class Solution {
public:
    bool containsDuplicate(vector<int>& nums){
        sort(nums.begin(),nums.end());
        for(int i=1;i<nums.size();i++){
            if(nums[i]==nums[i-1]){
                return true;
            }
            return false;
        }
    return 0; } 
};

EXPERIMENT 1.2 Contains Duplicate (219)
AIM:Given an integer array nums and an integer k, return true if there are two distinct indices i and j in the array such that nums[i] == nums[j] and abs(i - j) <= k.
ALGORITHM:
1.Create an empty hash map mp.
2.Traverse the array from index 0 to n-1.
3.For each element nums[i]:
4.Check if nums[i] already exists in the map.
5.If it exists:
6.Compute i - mp[nums[i]].
7.If this value is <= k, return true.
8.Update mp[nums[i]] = i.
9.After the loop ends, return false.
CODE:
class Solution {
public:
    bool containsNearbyDuplicate(vector<int>& nums, int k) {
        unordered_map<int, int> mp;

        for (int i = 0; i < nums.size(); i++) {
            if (mp.find(nums[i]) != mp.end()) {
                if (i - mp[nums[i]] <= k) {
                    return true;
                }
            }

            mp[nums[i]] = i;
        }

        return false;
    }
};
